race.comment: Competitive. SQUANDER (15) missed a whisker here and then at Ararat, both at this journey. Finally draws a low barrier and will get every chance to go one better. REBADGE (1) would be in the finish at best and third up is sure to show more. Has a couple of gear changes and he won't know himself back to 56 level. DANZAGRUNT (4) was on pace winning this grade at Tatura over 1980m. Has a wide gate but a sharp course striker is aboard, and the gelding is still shy of his best. COUSINS DAY (9) can show more third up and was vet cleared after he folded badly from the speed over 2000m at Warrnambool last time. She has more to give, and Yendall sticking aboard is a positive. Not sure of the riding tactics today but she has claims. TORBELO (16) ran an improved race, placing at Ararat in the SQUANDER race. Needs a good ride but is in the mix at a healthy price.
